  "doc_id": "31809",
  "text": "Instruments to assess teacher content knowledge for teaching have been developed [CITATION_1] , but these measures do not address beliefs, nor are they designed to give formative feedback to teachers. While these measures do address details of particular content areas, they do not shed light on the ways in which the mathematical knowledge may be understood, unpacked or developed by individuals, the details of how such understanding might be enhanced in teacher training programs, or the role of reflection and evolving beliefs. Thus the lack of measures of teachers' content knowledge may be a difficulty in determining what features of preservice education and later professional development contribute to teacher learning [CITATION_2] .",
